  "function_path": "source/common/router/upstream_request.cc",
  "function_name": "onPoolReady",
  "justification": "This function initializes an upstream request after its connection pool has successfully provided a connection. It takes ownership of a GenericUpstream via move semantics, a shared pointer to the upstream host description, a reference to the connection's address provider, a reference to the pool's stream info, and an optional HTTP protocol version. It performs all the described operations: records connection pool callback latency, reports successful connection to the host's outlier detector, sets protocol in stream info, copies connection timing data and stream count from the pool's stream info, sets up filter state with local/remote addresses and SSL info, synchronizes upstream and downstream byte meters, defers or starts per-try timeout setup based on downstream state, registers downstream watermark callbacks for backpressure, computes and starts the max stream duration timer, rewrites the Authority/Host header if auto-host-rewrite is enabled, emits an upstream pool-ready access log, and invokes all registered upstream connection established callbacks."
}

